{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Another striking observation in our multi-omics analysis is the activation of phospholipid metabolism throughout LEGO development.",
    "Interestingly, this activation is already noticeable in 1month-old LEGOs, supported by increased DHAP and G3P.",
    "DHAP is the intermediate metabolite of glycolysis and can be converted by GPD1 into G3P, the primary precursor for lipid metabolism.",
    "We have shown before that GPD1 is induced explicitly in brain tumor stem cells during brain tumor development and blocking GPD1 alters tumor lipid metabolism and prolongs the survival of brain tumor-bearing animals 30.",
    "The increase of DHAP, G3P, and CDPcholine in the metabolomic analysis and the increase of DG, TG, and PC in the lipidomic analysis in LEGOs demonstrate that lipid metabolism, particularly the glycerophospholipid metabolism, is activated during brain tumor development."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We have shown before that GPD1 is induced explicitly in brain tumor stem cells during brain tumor development and blocking GPD1 alters tumor lipid metabolism and prolongs the survival of brain tumor-bearing animals 30."
  ]
